<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Could we allow hyphen (-) in the charset in <em>Zend_Form_Element</em>'s <em>filterName()</em> function?</p>

<p>Or have the ability to manually set the ID of the label's HtmlTag's Decorator?  It currently relies on the element's name:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
// Zend_Form_Decorator_Label
// render()
        if (null !== $tag) {
            require_once 'Zend/Form/Decorator/HtmlTag.php';
            $decorator = new Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag();
            $decorator-&gt;setOptions(array('tag' =&gt; $tag,
                                         'id'  =&gt; $this-&gt;getElement()-&gt;getName() . '-label'));

            $label = $decorator-&gt;render($label);
        }
</code></pre>

<p>May be overkill, but I want to prepend the form's id to all the element, dt, and dd ids.</p>

<p>Trying to achieve the following:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Email Address


</code></pre>

<p>But does this instead:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Email Address


</code></pre>

<p>I haven't had much luck with an easy work around for the label's ID.  Any suggestions other than using custom decorators?</p>

